Every Commit Holds a Single Tree in Git
Blobs are files without metadata, Trees are Directories that hold blobs or trees
Staged(kinda like performance stage) work is the un saved worn
git commit -m "bla" ~= nn=$(echo "bla" | git commit-tree $(git write-tree))
echo $nn > .git/refs/heads/master(dangereous) use  'git update-ref .git/refs/head/master $nn' insted, this will register this commit as the head of the branch 'master' and this tracks the most recent commit made to 'master' branch.
1st commit dont have parent commit.
git symbolic-ref HEAD refs/heads/master, but for some reason i forgot this and it worked just fine.
git branch shows all available braches and commits that are dont have cildren and not a branch(named) while git show-brach=git log --all --oneline --graph shows all the commits available.
git checkout <commit hash> moves HEAD to that hash, git log shows the past(all the ansistors in an order) of the present commit, There are a lot of sorting and searching u can do which im not intrested in for now.
I donot understand git merge and git rebase properly i guess. Ill look into it later.
git replace --graft <TARGET_COMMIT_HASH> <EXISTING_PARENT_HASH> <ADDITIONAL_PARENT_HASH> to chnage parent of a commit.
git reset --hard HEAD~1 is set to deleate the present HEAD, idk how true, there is also a --soft option which idk how to use for now.
git status shows all the chnages made with respect to HEAD.
git commit -m 'bla' = git update-ref refs/heads/master $(echo 'bla' | git commit-tree -p HEAD $(git write-tree))
-S for commit-tree and commit will sign the commit cryptographically!
git log --show-signature to verify signature.
git config user.signingkey to verify the signing key, it should be a keyid string(all caps): FF2DF70EB208A53A52D77140EF585FDD26A0DD75
